This paper presents a method for learning policies for traffic signal controllers using deep reinforcement learning, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques to optimize traffic schedules, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also deals with robotics and control systems, which makes cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. The paper involves the use of systems and control theory to optimize traffic schedules, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of computer vision techniques to analyze traffic data, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible category.
